---
import SEO from '../components/SEO.astro';
import Navigation from '../components/Navigation.astro';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <SEO
    title="Placement Agent Fees | PE Fundraising Cost Guide 2025"
    description="Comprehensive guide to placement agent fees and costs. Learn about retainers, success fees, and typical fee structures for private equity fundraising."
  />
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700;800;900&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

  <style is:inline>
    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
    body {
      font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
      background: #000;
      color: #fff;
      line-height: 1.6;
      overflow-x: hidden;
    }

    .hero {
      min-height: 50vh;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 160px 40px 80px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.15), rgba(240, 147, 251, 0.15), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.95));
    }

    .hero-content { max-width: 900px; }

    .hero h1 {
      font-size: clamp(36px, 6vw, 56px);
      font-weight: 900;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff, #f093fb);
      background-clip: text;
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      line-height: 1.1;
    }

    .hero p {
      font-size: 20px;
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .content-section {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 80px 40px;
    }

    .content-block {
      margin-bottom: 60px;
    }

    .content-block h2 {
      font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 36px);
      font-weight: 800;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      color: #fff;
    }

    .content-block p {
      font-size: 17px;
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    .fee-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin: 24px 0;
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
      border-radius: 12px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .fee-table th, .fee-table td {
      padding: 16px 20px;
      text-align: left;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    }

    .fee-table th {
      background: rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.2);
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #fff;
    }

    .fee-table td {
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
    }

    .fee-table tr:last-child td {
      border-bottom: none;
    }

    .highlight-box {
      background: rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.1);
      border-left: 4px solid #667eea;
      padding: 24px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      margin: 32px 0;
    }

    .highlight-box p {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    .content-block ul {
      list-style: none;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }

    .content-block ul li {
      font-size: 17px;
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
      padding-left: 28px;
      position: relative;
    }

    .content-block ul li::before {
      content: '→';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: #667eea;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .cta-section {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.1), rgba(240, 147, 251, 0.1));
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.2);
      padding: 80px 40px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .cta-section h2 {
      font-size: clamp(28px, 5vw, 40px);
      font-weight: 900;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .cta-section p {
      font-size: 18px;
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
      margin-bottom: 28px;
      max-width: 600px;
      margin-left: auto;
      margin-right: auto;
    }

    .cta-button {
      display: inline-block;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea, #764ba2);
      color: #fff;
      padding: 18px 40px;
      border-radius: 100px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 16px;
      transition: all 0.3s;
    }

    .cta-button:hover {
      transform: translateY(-3px);
      box-shadow: 0 15px 40px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.4);
    }

    footer {
      padding: 60px 40px 30px;
      background: #000;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
      text-align: center;
    }

    footer p {
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
      font-size: 14px;
    }

    footer a {
      color: #667eea;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      nav { padding: 20px 30px; }
      .nav-links { display: none; }
      .hero { padding: 140px 30px 60px; }
      .content-section { padding: 60px 30px; }
      .fee-table { font-size: 14px; }
      .fee-table th, .fee-table td { padding: 12px 14px; }
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <Navigation />

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <h1>Placement Agent Fees</h1>
      <p>Understanding the cost structure of private equity fundraising advisors</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Typical Fee Structure</h2>
      <p>Placement agent compensation typically consists of two components: an upfront retainer and a success-based fee tied to capital raised. Fee structures vary based on fund size, strategy, and the agent's track record.</p>

      <table class="fee-table">
        <tr>
          <th>Fee Component</th>
          <th>Typical Range</th>
          <th>Notes</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Retainer Fee</td>
          <td>$25,000 - $100,000</td>
          <td>Monthly or quarterly; covers operational costs</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Success Fee</td>
          <td>1.0% - 2.0%</td>
          <td>Percentage of capital raised from agent-sourced LPs</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Tail Period</td>
          <td>12 - 24 months</td>
          <td>Fee protection for leads generated during engagement</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <p><strong>Market Benchmark:</strong> For funds under $500M, success fees typically range from 1.5-2.0%. Larger funds ($1B+) often negotiate fees of 1.0-1.5% due to economies of scale and competitive dynamics.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Fee Variations by Fund Size</h2>
      <p>Placement agent fees typically scale inversely with fund size:</p>

      <table class="fee-table">
        <tr>
          <th>Fund Size</th>
          <th>Success Fee Range</th>
          <th>Retainer</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Under $250M</td>
          <td>1.75% - 2.0%</td>
          <td>$25,000 - $50,000</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>$250M - $500M</td>
          <td>1.5% - 1.75%</td>
          <td>$50,000 - $75,000</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>$500M - $1B</td>
          <td>1.25% - 1.5%</td>
          <td>$75,000 - $100,000</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Over $1B</td>
          <td>1.0% - 1.25%</td>
          <td>Negotiated</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Additional Fee Considerations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Expense Reimbursement:</strong> Travel, accommodation, and marketing materials are typically reimbursed separately</li>
        <li><strong>Tiered Structures:</strong> Some agents offer declining rates above certain thresholds (e.g., 1.5% on first $300M, 1.0% thereafter)</li>
        <li><strong>Exclusive vs. Non-Exclusive:</strong> Exclusive mandates may command slightly higher fees but provide dedicated focus</li>
        <li><strong>Geographic Carve-Outs:</strong> Fees may vary by region, with higher rates for harder-to-access markets</li>
        <li><strong>Affiliate Fee Structures:</strong> Some firms offer reduced fees for re-ups or affiliated fund vehicles</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Negotiation Factors</h2>
      <p>Several factors influence fee negotiations:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Manager's track record and existing LP relationships</li>
        <li>Strategy complexity and market appetite</li>
        <li>Target raise size and timeline</li>
        <li>Competitive dynamics among placement agents</li>
        <li>Scope of services (full mandate vs. targeted regional coverage)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block">
      <h2>Value vs. Cost</h2>
      <p>While fees represent a meaningful cost, successful placement agents often deliver significant value through faster closes, access to hard-to-reach LPs, market intelligence, and strategic positioning advice. The key is ensuring alignment between the agent's capabilities and your fund's specific needs.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <h2>Compare Placement Agents</h2>
    <p>Research top placement agents and their service offerings in our comprehensive directory</p>
    <a href="/private-equity-placement-agents-list" class="cta-button">Browse Directory</a>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <p>© 2025 <a href="/">Placement</a>. Your guide to <a href="/">top private equity placement agents</a>.</p>
    <p style="font-size: 12px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); margin-top: 16px;">Placement Quest is a financial news site. Nothing on this site should be considered financial advice.</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
